Underwater selfies by @sierrasonshine 🤩 Just a reminder of some FAQs about Devil’s Den:
1. We offer both snorkeling and scuba diving - It is required that all guests wear their snorkel, masks, and fins for snorkeling, and the rest of their gear for scuba diving during their entire visit!
2. Guests MUST be at least six years old to enter the Den. Guests under the age of 18 MUST be accompanied by their guardian. If you will be accompanied by another chaperone other than your guardian, you must use the permission slip on our website!
3. We definitely do NOT have sharks OR alligators in the Den. Haha. Just some fish and some turtles!
4. We do not allow dogs on the property! We have some animals that live on our property full-time, and to avoid any confrontations, we ask that our guests’ furry friends stay home!
5. If some members of your party are not strong swimmers, or do not want to snorkel/scuba dive at the Den, there is a gorgeous botanical garden right next door to us called @cedarlakeswoodsandgardens with lots of plants and even a beautiful waterfall! It’s a great place for our guests who are waiting for their friends/family to finish their snorkeling reservations!
These are some answers to questions we’ve been getting a lot lately! Hope this helps! And if I didn’t answer your question, please feel free to reach out and ask! 😊🤿
